Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportTranViolation(25.10)                          reportTranViolation(25.10)

Name
       reportTranViolation  -  After  timing  analysis, reports pins and ports
       that exceed the transition constraints in the timing constraints file

Syntax
       reportTranViolation

       [-help]

       [-all | -noGlobalNets]

       [-max]

       [-min]

       [-selNetFile <fileName>]

       [-excNetFile <fileName>]

       [-significant_digits]

       [-useDrcMargin]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       After timing analysis, reports pins and ports that exceed  the  transi-
       tion constraints in the timing constraints file.

       Run  this  command after running timing analysis (timeDesign) or timing
       optimization (optDesign).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportTranViolation parameter.  For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man reportTranViolation

       -all   Reports violations on all nets in the design.

              Default: -all

       -excNetFile <fileName>
              Specifies a file that lists the names hierarchical nets that are
              excluded from the transition violation report.

       -noGlobalNets
              Reports violations on all nets except for power and ground nets.

              Note: The parameters, -all and -noGlobalNets are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -max   Reports violations of maximum transition constraints.

       -min   Reports violations of minimum transition constraints.

              Note: The parameters, -max and -min are mutually exclusive.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies name of the output file.

       -selNetFile<fileName>
              Specifies a file that lists the names of  hierarchical  nets  to
              consider in the transition violation report.

              Note:  The parameters, -selNetFile and -excNetFile are not mutu-
              ally exclusive. If both parameters are specified,  the  -excNet-
              File parameter overides the -selNetFile parameter.

       -significant_digits
              Allows the user to specify the number of significant digits.

              Default: 3

       -useDrcMargin
              Generates  a report using the margin value that you specify with
              the -drcMargin parameter of the  setOptMode command.

Example
       The following command runs timing analysis and generates a module1.tran
       report file that lists the pins and ports that  exceed  the  transition
       constraints:

       reportTranViolation -outfile module1.tran

